<font color="#FF0000">CHRIS, FRESH MEAT, NO OFFENSE.</font><br>
<tt>Wed Mar 12 21:36:48 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Chris's idealism and sincerity is refreshing but<br>
very familiar. His contribution is most welcome.<br><br>
Chris, some of your refrains have such a familiar<br>
ring and harkens to the polarization that occured<br>
to our generation. We were passionate. It led our<br>
generation to making vast assumptions, to both those<br>
who served and those who decided not to. Each found<br>
justifications for what they did, be it pointing the<br>
finger at a government that is of course a beauracracy,<br>
to those who served who tried to find meaning in<br>
what they experienced.<br><br>
I don't mindlessly trust my government. It consists<br>
of us, humans. On the other hand it is not a immoral<br>
entity by virtue of existence. All levels of care,<br>
competency and ineptitude exists in its fold. That has<br>
not changed. To point to the eco-industrial-military-<br>
political complex as some sort of evil entity does not<br>
serve us as a community. Trust it, NO. Cast it as evil<br>
incarnate, NO.<br><br>
Those thrust into War's path come with each generation.<br>
The global community has not come close to finding a<br>
path to avoid it, rather it searches it out. The USA<br>
is not some demon. We, and by the way you, and all of us<br>
are the USA - government and all. Great soldier, even<br>
though they may seem autocratic, are a blessing as much<br>
as a Martin Luther King are to our society. They lead<br>
us, the unwashed masses through events beyond our control.<br><br>
Remember, don't trust those polarized to some idealized<br>
vision of world peace, human dignity, and total productivity<br>
any more than the evils so easy to spot in our governmental<br>
system and economic system that keeps us in any profitable<br>
enterprise.<br><br>
They are just as wrong as right. Just like the government.<br><br>
As for us Vets, We rehash the intricate circumstances that<br>
led each of us to a very personal trauma. We dissect it.<br>
We turn it in our hands, heads, and hearts. It is our<br>
essence.<br><br>
Stay cool, young person. You shall become jaded, and yet<br>
enriched. Come anytime to probe what is here. You are<br>
welcome here and eagerly read.<br><br>

<p><code>-- carnival@ont.com  (JJ the Boonirat) </code><p>


